                   "message":  "ai-dispatch ISSUE-258: in-app Open GLB (Ctrl+O)\n\nClose the Phase 9 editor-usability gap where content was only loadable\nvia --scene/--glb CLI args. Ctrl+O now opens a native file dialog to\nload a .glb from inside the running editor.\n\n- rfd native dialog owned by rge-editor only; editor-shell gains no\n  rfd/rge-io-gltf edge. New GlbOpenDialog trait mirrors AssetReloadHook.\n- EditorShell::handle_open_request: pick .glb -\u003e load -\u003e swap, committing\n  glb_source_path ONLY after reload_glb + reload_render_assets both\n  succeed; failed/cancelled open leaves the prior path and frame intact.\n- Both hooks attached in all launch modes so Ctrl+O works from any scene.\n- GLB-only: no scene/project open, no runtime World swap, no Save,\n  drag-drop, or MenuRegistry. Watcher untouched (stays bound to the\n  original --glb path; only manual R-key reload follows an opened file).\n- 6 tests: failing-candidate leaves path unchanged, success commits,\n  cancel / no-dialog / non-Editing no-ops, end-to-end GPU swap.\n\nPer ai_handoffs/ISSUE-258 TASK + CORRECT packets.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
